  "updateinfo_id": "ALSA-2026:39576",
  "description": "The SMB/CIFS protocol is a standard file sharing protocol widely deployed on Microsoft Windows machines. The cifs-utils packages contain tools for mounting shares on Linux using the SMB/CIFS protocol. The tools in this package work in conjunction with support in the kernel to allow one to mount a SMB/CIFS share onto a client and use it as if it were a standard Linux file system.  \n\nSecurity Fix(es):  \n\n  * cifs-utils: local privilege escalation via forged cifs.spnego key description in cifs.upcall (CVE-2026-12505)\n\n\nBug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s):  \n\n  * cifs-utils: regression with kerberos mount [almalinux-9.8.z] (JIRA:AlmaLinux-192982)\n\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n",
  "fromstr": "packager@almalinux.org",
